            <fr:title text="Intersection and union">Intersection and union</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Given sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex>, their <html:strong>intersection</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \cap  \Delta ]]></fr:tex> is the set whose members are exactly the things that are members of <html:em>both</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex>.
Their <html:strong>union</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma  \cup  \Delta ]]></fr:tex> is the set whose members are exactly the things that are members of <html:em>either</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta ]]></fr:tex>.
(Remember <fr:link href="/lectures/000E/" title="Logicians' Weird Habit 1" uri="https://negation.rocks/lectures/000E/" display-uri="000E" type="local">logicians' weird habit 1</fr:link> here!)</html:p>
